pplied to the CX innovation problem. The authors draw on hundreds of CX design and strategic innovation projects across a range of industries, both B2B and B2C, from primary research through client work and secondary case studies available in the public domain. The examples include many different vertical industry sectors, including those involving hybrid business models. The cases included share what worked really well and where CX failed. The content goes beyond what actually happened to present an idea of what might be possible with the right design approach and committed resources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCustomer relations. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aAgile Marketing.  aAmbidexterity.  aCustomer Experience Management.  aLean Management.  aStrategic Innovation.1 aAllen, Cyrus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBej, George, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDew, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Bill, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWilliams, Macgregor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2021 Englishz978311075404908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2021z9783110753820oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz9783110684025